content: Rubbish app that barely works on my nexus 7.  I'll plug in my USB and it will access the files I want fine the FIRST Time but if I unplug the USB or close the program it won't work saying either "USB plug in app not working"  or give me some script error.   Then I must restart my Nexus 7 and it'll work again...  I've tried everything from stopping the program  from task manager and nothing works besides reboot. I know it isn't my device because it's flawless.
replyContent:
Hello Charles, this is not normal. Please do the following:
1. Uninstall and Reinstall the plugin
2. Start the plugin as an app. The Settings page appears
2. Uncheck the option "Autostart"
3. In the USB-Attach-Dialog do not select "Always open"
4. After the next error go back to the Settings page and click on "Send Problem Report via Mail"

content: At first I had problems with the plugin not recognizing my USB, turns out my Sandisk Cruzer USB wont get recognized because it has an additional partition (U3 drive), now i tried it with another USB with single partition and the plugin works flawlessly. Developer was very helpful and quick with his reply to my emails. I now give the plugin 5 star because  it is just amazing. Thank you very much.
replyContent:
We located the problem. The Stick has U3 hardware. 
A new release supporting U3 is available for the free release of the plugin.
If testing is successfull the patch will be adopted to the full version.
